    "summary": "I got my Bachelor's in Mathematics at the University of Liege with highest praise. After that, I decided to join the Master of Logic at the Institute for Logic, Language and Computation (ILLC) in Amsterdam, and specialised in abstract mathematics and theoretical computer science. I successfully defended my thesis titled \"Hereditary structural completeness of weakly transitive modal logics\" in August 2023, and graduated from the Master of Logic with a GPA of 8.76/10.\nI am now going to join the University of Luxembourg as a PhD student, where I hope to keep researching logic, algebra and topology, as well as the connections between these topics.\n\nI also have some experience in programming. Throughout my education, I mastered languages such as Python, C, Java and Haskell and acquired skills such as object-oriented programming, functional programming and formal verification (using proof assistants).\nMy theoretical computer science knowledge ranges over lambda calculus, various type theories, automata theory and complexity theory.\n\nFor a survey of my writing samples, please have a look at my personal webpage. For an overview of my programming projects, you can consult my GitHub profile.",
